.so ../bk-macros
.TH "bk root" "\*[BKVER]" %E% "\*(BC" "\*(UM"
.SH NAME
bk root \- print the path name to the root of the repository
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bk root
.[ARG] "directory \fB|\fP file"
.SH DESCRIPTION
This command prints the full pathname to the root of the repository.
The following commands are equivalent:
.DS
bk root
bk -R pwd
.DE
.LP
If a directory or file is specified,
.B bk root
will try to find the 
project root of that file or directory.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.LP
.B bk root
returns exit status:
.TP
0
on success.
.tp
1
on failure.
.SH CATEGORY
.B Admin
